Arsenal are currently on top of the Premier League table with five points ahead of Manchester City, who are in second position. The Gunners will move eight points clear on top of the Premier League table if they beat Tottenham Hotspur on Sunday. Mikel Arteta’s side have so far played 17 Premier League matches – won 14, drew two and lost one. They have 44 points from 17 league matches. Behind Arsenal are Man City, who have 39 points from 18 games after losing to Manchester United in Saturday’s derby at Old Trafford. Man United are in third position with 38 points from 18 games. Behind the Red Devils are Newcastle United (fourth), Tottenham Hotspur (fifth) and Fulham (sixth). Others are Brighton (seventh), Brentford (eighth), Liverpool (ninth) and Chelsea (tenth).